7 SECTION 2. Arkansas Code § 7-6-208(d), concerning reports not required
8 for candidates for a county office and resulting from Initiated Act 1 of
9 1996, is amended to read as follows:
10 (d) Reports Not Required.
11 (1) A candidate who has not received contributions or made
12 expenditures in excess of five hundred dollars ($500) shall not be required
13 to file any preelection reports required under subdivision (a)(1) of this
14 section. In calculating the amount of contributions received or expenditures
15 made for purposes of this exception, the payment of the filing fee from the
16 candidate's personal funds shall not be considered as either a contribution
17 or an expenditure.
18 (2) The preelection reports referenced in subdivision (a)(1) of
19 this section are only required only for candidates with opponents in those
20 elections.
